{% extends "./internal/base.njk" %}

{% block main %}

<h1>Rough Elements</h1>
<p>A robust set of common UI elements with a hand-drawn, sketchy look.</p>

<p>
  The elements are drawn with enough randomness that no two renderings will
  be exactly the same, just like two separate hand-drawn shapes.  They are
  heavily inspired by <a href="https://wiredjs.com/">Wired Wlements</a> and
  <a href="https://shoelace.style/">Shoelace</a>.
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Works with all frameworks</li>
  <li>Works with CDNs</li>
  <li>Fully customizable with CSS</li>
  <li>Includes a dark theme</li>
  <li>Open source</li>
</ul>

<h2>Quick Start</h2>
Add the following to your webpage.
<pre>
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@rogerta/rough-element@1/dist/themes/light.css" /&gt;
&lt;script type="module" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@rogerta/rough-element@1/dist/rough-elements.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>

<h1>Attribution</h1>
<ul>
<li>Components are built with Lit</li>
<li>Component metadata is generated by the Custom Elements Manifest Analyzer</li>
<li>Documentation is powered by 11ty</li>
<li>CDN services are provided by jsDelivr</li>
</ul>

{% endblock %}
